<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcfbca250-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0" identifier="/us/usc/t48/s1955"><num value="1955">§ 1955.</num><heading> Audit certification</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The chief officer of any agency conducting an audit pursuant to paragraph (1) of sections 1902(c) and 1903(m) of this title and <ref href="/us/usc/t48/s1931/d/1/C">section 1931(d)(1)(C) of this title</ref> shall certify that audit.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idcfbca251-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/219/tI/s106">Pub. L. 101–219, title I, § 106</ref>, <date date="1989-12-12">Dec. 12, 1989</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/103/1871">103 Stat. 1871</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idcfbca252-3a70-11f1-9e44-df1065572ea0">
